Hello,

I am referring to the book "Integrating and Extending BIRT", page 189 to write a simple standalone Java application to call the BIRT engine.  Here is the code:

        IReportRunnable report = null;
        ReportEngine engine = null;

        try {
            EngineConfig config = new EngineConfig();
            config.setEngineHome("C:/Program Files/birt-runtime-2_1_1/ReportEngine");
            PlatformFileContext fileContext = new PlatformFileContext();
            config.setPlatformContext(fileContext);
            HTMLCompleteImageHandler imageHandler = new HTMLCompleteImageHandler();
            HTMLEmitterConfig htmlEmitterConfig = new HTMLEmitterConfig();
            htmlEmitterConfig.setImageHandler(imageHandler);
            config.setEmitterConfiguration(RenderOptionBase.OUTPUT_FORMAT_HTML, htmlEmitterConfig);
            engine = new ReportEngine(config);
        }
        catch(Throwable err) {
            System.err.println(err);
        }

When I try to create a new ReportEngine object (last statement), the following exception is thrown:

org.eclipse.birt.core.exception.BirtException: $NO-RB$ Cant startup the OSGI framework
	at org.eclipse.birt.core.framework.Platform.startup(Platform.java:90)
	at org.eclipse.birt.core.framework.Platform.initialize(Platform.java:116)
	at org.eclipse.birt.report.engine.api.ReportEngine.<init>(ReportEngine.java:49)
	at com.packeteer.pljava.test.BirtReportGenerator.initialize(BirtReportGenerator.java:38)
	at com.packeteer.pljava.test.BirtReportGenerator.<init>(BirtReportGenerator.java:22)
	at com.packeteer.pljava.test.BirtReportGenerator.main(BirtReportGenerator.java:47)
Caused by: org.eclipse.birt.core.exception.BirtException: $NO-RB$ Could not find the Framework - [Ljava.lang.Object;@183f74d
	at org.eclipse.birt.core.framework.osgi.OSGILauncher.startup(OSGILauncher.java:88)
	at org.eclipse.birt.core.framework.Platform.startup(Platform.java:78)
	... 5 more
Can't load the report engine

Any ideas to the source of the problem?  I am using version 2.1.1.  Thanks.

Cheers,

Fred

As it turns out for BIRT version 2.1.1, one should use

IReportEngineFactory factory =
    (IReportEngineFactory) Platform.createFactoryObject(
    IReportEngineFactory.EXTENSION_REPORT_ENGINE_FACTORY);
engine = factory.createReportEngine(config);

to create an object of IReportEngine.  Do not use "new ReportEngine(config)" as this is apparently outdated and the source of the problem.
